Four improvements to the multi-repo surface built on v0.2.0 foundations:

1. Batch export (export --all [--kind <k>] --audience <a>)
   - Iterates all notes in source ref, optional kind filter
   - Respects public export policy, adds exported-from edge
   - Idempotent: re-running exports same count
   - Works with --slot for slot-scoped export

2. list-imports command
   - User-facing surface for what was only accessible via raw git refs
   - Shows name, note count, fetch date, source remote
   - Remote extracted from import wrapper commit message

3. Foreign object labels
   - obj_label() now shows [foreign:oid] instead of ??:oid
   - Affects find, doctor, and any command displaying imported objects

4. Test suite: test-multi-repo-phase2.sh (22 assertions)
   - Batch export: all, kind filter, slot, empty, idempotent, policy
   - list-imports: empty, single, multiple, remote discovery
   - Foreign labels: find and doctor output

All 389 tests pass (267 core + 61 phase0 + 39 phase1 + 22 phase2).
